# Vercel access (Cursor agent)

Account **adamripon-6504** on team **adamripon-6504's projects** (`adamripon-6504s-projects`, id `team_Xq24x8kEPHB8f71YZLIZsmic`).

## How Cursor gets Vercel access

Cursor does **not** have a separate Vercel login. The agent uses:

1. **Vercel MCP** (`plugin-vercel-vercel`) — OAuth via the Vercel Cursor plugin (deployments, projects, logs, env, docs)
2. **`npx vercel`** — same account as `vercel whoami` / `vercel login` on this machine
3. Optional **`VERCEL_TOKEN`** in local `.env` (gitignored) — [Full Account](https://vercel.com/account/tokens) token for REST API / SDK when MCP or CLI is insufficient

Re-authenticate MCP: **Cursor Settings → MCP → Vercel → Connect / Reconnect**.

## Agent permissions (do freely)

- List/create/link projects; deploy preview and production (`deploy_to_vercel`, `npx vercel deploy`, `npx vercel --prod`)
- Read build/runtime logs; inspect and promote/rollback deployments
- Manage env vars (`vercel env pull|add|rm`, dashboard-equivalent via API when needed)
- Domains, redirects, project settings, and team-scoped project config
- Marketplace integrations and linked resources (Supabase, storage, etc.) on this team
- Use `/vercel status`, `/vercel env`, `/vercel deploy` plugin commands when relevant

Default scope for CLI/MCP: `--scope adamripon-6504s-projects` when a scope is required.

## Commands

```bash
npx vercel@latest whoami
npx vercel@latest teams ls
npx vercel@latest project ls --scope adamripon-6504s-projects
npx vercel@latest link --yes --scope adamripon-6504s-projects   # when working in a Vercel app repo
npx vercel@latest deploy
npx vercel@latest env pull .env.local --yes
```

## Never

- Paste tokens or PATs into chat, commits, or rules
- Delete the Vercel account or change team billing without explicit confirmation
- Deploy this **lurafi** Shopify theme to Vercel unless the user explicitly asks (store deploy is Shopify — see `docs/SHOPIFY.md`)

